## How to use this system

**Starting from the file you're editing, walk upward through the
directory tree. Read every `DESIGN.md` and `BEST_PRACTICES.md` you
encounter, as deeply as the current task requires. Don't stop at the
first one — the relevant context for a cross-cutting change often
lives two or three levels up.**

<% services.forEach((svc) => { -%>
### Working inside `<%= svc.name %>`

<% if (svc.mobile && svc.mobile.enabled) { -%>
When editing a file in `<%= svc.name %>/mobile/src/services/`:

1. Read `DESIGN.md` at the project root (cross-service architecture).
2. Read `<%= svc.name %>/mobile/DESIGN.md` (mobile app architecture).
3. Read `<%= svc.name %>/mobile/src/services/BEST_PRACTICES.md`
   (service conventions).
4. Continue reading upward if the task spans more than one folder.

<% } -%>
<% if (svc.web && svc.web.enabled) { -%>
When editing a file in `<%= svc.name %>/web/src/lib/`:

1. Read `DESIGN.md` at the project root (cross-service architecture).
2. Read `<%= svc.name %>/web/DESIGN.md` (web app architecture).
3. Read `<%= svc.name %>/web/src/lib/BEST_PRACTICES.md` (library
   conventions).
4. Continue reading upward if the task spans more than one folder.

<% } -%>
When editing a file in `<%= svc.name %>/backend/controllers/rest-api/routes/`:

1. Read `DESIGN.md` at the project root (cross-service architecture).
2. Read `<%= svc.name %>/backend/DESIGN.md` (service architecture).
3. Read `<%= svc.name %>/backend/controllers/rest-api/DESIGN.md`
   (server boot sequence, request flow).
4. Read `<%= svc.name %>/backend/controllers/rest-api/routes/BEST_PRACTICES.md`
   (thin handlers, schema imports, auth hooks).
5. Continue reading upward if the task spans more than one folder.

<% }); -%>

The hierarchy flows: **Project root → Service root → Subsystem → Feature folder**.

