## Cross-service boundaries

The `auth` service is the trust anchor. Non-auth services verify
requests by forwarding cookies to
`${AUTH_SERVICE_URL}/api/auth/get-session`. Never add user or session
tables outside the auth service — always use the forwarded `user`
decorated on the request.

## Key principle

**DESIGN.md = "Why and how things are structured"**
**BEST_PRACTICES.md = "How to write code here"**

Agents should always check for these files before making changes,
**starting from the most specific (current folder) and reading upward
through the hierarchy as deeply as the task requires**. Don't stop at
the first file you find — scan upward until you've covered every level
that the change touches.

